---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Professional Experience | AJ Gamble"
	description="Proven track record in operational leadership and process optimization."
	heroImage="/Gemini_copy_Generated_Image_2r54f22r54f22r54.jpg"
>
	<h1>Proven Operational Track Record</h1>
	<p>
		I believe that operational excellence is not a state of being, but a continuous process of refinement. Below are specific case studies demonstrating how I have navigated operational chaos and delivered measurable results.
	</p>
<section style="margin: 4rem 0; padding: 3rem; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 8px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Operational Case Study: McKissick Products</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem;">
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Challenge</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">Fragmented communication between production planning and shop floor personnel led to unrealistic scheduling, low morale, and poor accountability.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Strategic Intervention</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">Implemented <strong>radical transparency</strong> by posting real-time performance metrics in the shop. Established a daily cross-functional synchronization meeting to negotiate capacity and balance workloads.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid #000;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem;">The Bottom Line Result</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold;">On-Time Delivery Performance increased from <span style="color: #d00;">55%</span> to <span style="color: #080;">95%</span>.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section style="margin: 4rem 0; padding: 3rem; background: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 8px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Strategic Scaling: The Crosby Group</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem;">
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Challenge</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">The organization lacked visibility into the full manufacturing lifecycle—from raw material to final shipment—creating a disconnect between Sales promises and Production realities.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Strategic Intervention</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">I bridged the gap by acting as an operational translator, leveraging my shop-floor experience to dismantle silos. I implemented a robust KPI framework including OTIF (On-Time In-Full) shipments, quote turnaround, and region-specific growth tracking.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid #000;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem;">The Bottom Line Result</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold;">Scaled annual revenue from <span style="color: #d00;">$31M</span> to <span style="color: #080;">$82M</span> within 4 years.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section style="margin: 4rem 0; padding: 3rem; background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; border-radius: 8px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Operational Excellence: Industrial Splicing</h2>
        
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 3rem;">
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Challenge</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">Managed internal sales and production coordination in a high-pressure rigging shop environment characterized by siloed communication and strained relations between office and floor staff.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">The Strategic Intervention</h3>
                <p style="color: #555;">Transformed workflow by establishing two-way communication channels with production management, balancing customer delivery promises with shop capacity, and maintaining a "hands-on" presence on the floor to foster mutual respect.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid #000;">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem;">The Bottom Line Result</h3>
            <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: bold;">Achieved <span style="color: #080;">$1.2M</span> in annual sales (2025)—outperforming the next highest agent by over 30%—and secured high-level trust with key industrial accounts like Zeeco through consistent, reliable data accuracy.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 4rem 0;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Career Timeline</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: none; padding: 0; border-left: 2px solid #ddd; margin-left: 0.5rem;">
            <li style="padding: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative;">
                <strong>Inside Sales Associate II</strong> — Industrial Splicing and Sling LLC <span style="color: #888;">(2024–2026)</span>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative;">
                <strong>CNC Machine Operator</strong> — Wood Systems <span style="color: #888;">(2023–2024)</span>
                <p style="color: #888; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Set up and operated CNC machinery to manufacture precision components, interpreting production tickets and technical documentation to ensure exact dimensional accuracy.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative;">
                <strong>CNC Machine Operator</strong> — Southern Millwork, Inc. <span style="color: #888;">(2017–2023)</span>
                <p style="color: #888; margin: 0.25rem 0 0;">Operated precision horizontal mills to exacting industrial specifications, building a hands-on foundation in manufacturing processes and quality control that continues to inform how I approach operations leadership today.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: 0 0 1.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative;">
                <strong>Manager of International Operations and Inside Sales</strong> — The Crosby Group <span style="color: #888;">(2011–2015)</span>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: 0 0 0 1.5rem; position: relative;">
                <strong>Production Planner</strong> — McKissick Products (The Crosby Group) <span style="color: #888;">(2007–2011)</span>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section style="margin: 4rem 0; padding: 3rem; background: #f9f9f9; border-radius: 8px;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">What Colleagues Say</h2>
        <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem;">
            <blockquote style="margin: 0; font-style: italic; color: #333;">
                "A.J. is an assertive, dedicated, task-oriented individual who would be an asset to any professional team, group, or organization. He is very self-motivated by his pride and his desire to be part of a successful project. I have worked with A.J. on multiple corporate-level project teams, and I am very impressed by his strong contributions."
                <footer style="margin-top: 1rem; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">— Darin Herndon, Operations Manager at MP Innovations LLC</footer>
            </blockquote>
            <blockquote style="margin: 0; font-style: italic; color: #333;">
                "A.J. is a very detail-oriented person who works to streamline processes for maximum efficiency... A.J. is not a 'band-aid' type of person, he fixes the problem. He is a hard charger that would be extremely valuable to any organization that needs to bring order to chaos, or is looking to increase customer satisfaction and sales. I would highly recommend him for a senior position in any company!"
                <footer style="margin-top: 1rem; font-style: normal; font-weight: bold;">— Steve Smith, Global Sales &amp; Growth Executive</footer>
            </blockquote>
        </div>
    </section>
    </Layout>